// C FFI fixed-size array support.
//
// The compiler supports fixed-size arrays for C-compatible struct fields
// via the `field_name[N]` syntax in struct declarations. These produce
// `Array<T,N>` types in the type system, lowered to LLVM `[N x T]`
// (contiguous elements with no length prefix), matching C ABI layout.
//
// Usage in struct field declarations:
//     struct Foreign {
//         i32 values[4];   // Array<i32, 4>
//         f64 matrix[16];  // Array<f64, 16>
//     }
//
// This file is documentation only — the `Array<T,N>` type is handled
// directly by the compiler (parser → type system → codegen) and does
// not have a generic struct definition here.
//
// For runtime-dynamic contiguous buffers, use Slice<T> (std/slice.ag).
